## Code Simplification Report

### Changes Made

#### 1. Move `CONTACT_DATA_KEYS` to module scope
**File**: `frontend/src/components/DetailPanel.tsx`
**Type**: Removed redundancy / performance
**Before**:
```tsx
// Inside component body — new Set allocated every render
const CONTACT_DATA_KEYS = new Set(['email', 'phone', 'role', 'title', 'position'])
```
**After**:
```tsx
// Module-level constant — allocated once
const CONTACT_DATA_KEYS = new Set(['email', 'phone', 'role', 'title', 'position'])
```

---

#### 2. Extract IIFE contact card into `ContactCard` component
**File**: `frontend/src/components/DetailPanel.tsx:226-282`
**Type**: Reduced nesting / removed unusual pattern
**Before**:
```tsx
{thing.type_hint === 'person' && (() => {
  const email = thing.data?.email != null ? String(thing.data.email) : null
  // ... 50 more lines of logic + JSX inside an IIFE
  return (<div className="...">...</div>)
})()}
```
**After**:
```tsx
{thing.type_hint === 'person' && (
  <ContactCard title={thing.title} data={thing.data} />
)}
```
`ContactCard` is now a proper module-level component alongside `ThingLink`, following the established pattern in the file.

---

#### 3. Extract `direction` arrow from inner loop
**File**: `frontend/src/components/DetailPanel.tsx:80`
**Type**: Removed redundancy
**Before**: `const direction = '→'` allocated per loop iteration
**After**: `const REL_DIRECTION = '→'` at module scope, referenced in the loop

